This repository contains a collection of small Arduino-based projects developed during my BTech in Electronics and Communication Engineering.
Each file demonstrates how to interface Arduino with different sensors, actuators, and basic electronic components. Along with the code, corresponding circuit diagrams are also included.


📁 REPOSITORY CONTENTS

The repository currently includes the following projects:

🔘 Basic Digital Interfacing

💡 LDR (Light Sensor)

🔊 Buzzer

🌡 Temperature Sensor

📏 Ultrasonic Sensor

🚦 Traffic Light System

💧 Water Sensor

🔧 Servo Motor



🛠 TECHNOLOGIES USED

Arduino Uno

Embedded C (Arduino IDE)

Basic electronic components

Circuit design & sensor interfacing



🚀 HOW TO RUN

Clone this repository

Open the required .ino file in Arduino IDE

Connect the circuit as shown in the corresponding image

Upload the code to your Arduino board

Monitor output using Serial Monitor (if applicable)
